==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Strophe
<hw>Stro"phe</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Strophes</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[NL., from Gr. <?/, fr. <?/
to twist, to turn; perh. akin to E. <ets>strap</ets>.]</ety> <def>In
Greek choruses and dances, the movement of the chorus while turning from
the right to the left of the orchestra; hence, the strain, or part of
the choral ode, sung during this movement. Also sometimes used of a
stanza of modern verse. See the Note under
<er>Antistrophe</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Strophic</ent>⟦br⟧
